speech: JDK	: JDK stands for Java Development Kit.	JDK is used to compile and execute the Java package.	It consists of JRE + development tools.    JVM    : JVM stands for Java Virtual Machine.	It provides the specification for the runtime environment to run the bytecode of the java program.	It a superset that contains specification, Implementation, and runtime instances.	JRE : JRE stands for Java Runtime Environment. 	It provides the runtime environment to run the bytecode.   It is the virtual implementation of the JDK.

data.text: Explain the difference between the JDK, JRE, and JVM?
